race.comment: SUPERMASSIVE (7) was backed from 7.0 to 4.8 on debut last start and the money was almost right. The son of Snitzel settled just off the pace then powered late to miss by a neck at the end of 1200m at Kembla. Will take a lot from that run and he clearly looks the one to beat. FUADEE (1) showed good natural speed and held on well for second on debut over 1100m at Hawkesbury recently. Kept fresh since that run five weeks ago and will give a good account again. LA BASILIQUE (11) probably should have finished a touch closer when runner-up on debut over this distance at Kembla last start. In the mix with some improvement to come. SYLPH (13) returns from a six-month spell. Showed ability in the maiden campaign including a respectable effort at Listed level when she last appeared. Recent trial winner who can make an immediate impact. ICHIBAN KOJI (4) is first-up from an eight-month spell for Waller. Two trials will have him forward enough to run well. Market watch on debutant ADENAUER (2).
